The defendant Trevor R. Christian was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Trevor R. Christian is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Trevor R. Christian was found guilty of Take/Drive Veh. w/o Consent-Abandon Veh., a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

03:27 PM Defendant Trevor R. Christian in court in custody with attorney Steven G. Richards. Prosecuting Atty Curtis Johnson appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Court hears Johnson - he moves to amended count 1 to 943.23(3m) -Class A Misd operating a MV without xconsent of an owner but returned within 24 hours, and to dismiss the repeater enhancement; so ordered.  Johnson moves to dismiss count 2 - so ordered.  Court verbally reviews charges/penalties of amended count with the defendant.  Defendant pleads no contest to amended count 1.  Victim contact related.  Jury trial waived.  Defendant sworn.    Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form - colloquy given.  Defendant freely, willingly, knowledgeably and intelligently enters into the plea agreement and joint recommendation.  
Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1 as amended.  Court hears counsel, both request court adopt joint recommendation and give reasons.  Court enters sentence as follows:  Sentence Withheld, 2 years probation concurrent to all other counts, but consecutive to the federal sentence he is serving.  Probation begins at the conclusion fo the federal sentence.  Costs (including CPS fees) are all waived.  Counseling is ordered as recommendated by the agent.  Court advises of firearm restrictions because of felony, as well as voting restrictions.  Notice of Right to Seek Post Conviction Relief filed.
